The paper discusses techniques for result diversification in citation-based bibliographic search, which is a problem commonly studied in the information retrieval (IR) community. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of search engines, which falls under the categories of information retrieval and natural language processing (NLP), making cs.DL, cs.CL, and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses bibliographic search techniques, which are related to database systems (cs.DB).
